-- Mozambique's State Oil Company Signs Exploration Agreements, Noticias Says
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-06-18T07:19:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/mozambique-s-state-oil-company-signs-exploration-agreements-noticias-says.html

          
          
             Instituto Nacional de Petroleo,
Mozambiqueâ€™s state-run oil company, signed six agreements with
international oil companies to explore for oil and gas in the
southern African country,  Noticias  reported.  
 The companies include Aguila Energy Lda, Swiss Oil Holdings
International Ltd., DNO International ASA of Norway, New Age
(African Global Energy) Ltd., Sasol Petroleum International Ltd.
and Touchstone Oil and Gas Ltd., the Maputo-based newspaper
said, citing the institute.  
 The companies have six months to submit proposal on their
concessions, Noticias said.  
